cal pressure (IDP) and trunk muscle\nactivity (MA). Model predictions correlated highly with in vivo data (MTMS:\nr>=0.82, p<=0.03; LDC: r=0.77, p<0.001; IDP: r>=0.78, p<0.001; MA: r>=0.90,\np<0.001), indicating suitability for the reasonably accurate prediction of\nmaximal trunk muscle strength, segmental loading and trunk muscle activity in\nchildren and adolescents. When aiming at investigating children or adolescents\nwith pathologies such as idiopathic scoliosis, our models can serve as a basis\nfor the creation of deformed spine models and for comparative purposes.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 13 Jun 2019 17:05:30 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 15 Jan 2020 11:09:33 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-01-16"}
