k can cool the planet. The global radiation\nefficiencies are high (eta^phys > 97%) but the remainder of the total incoming\nenergy, which is brought into the planet, exceeds the internal luminosity of\nclassical cold starts by orders of magnitude. Overall, these findings suggest\nthat warm or hot starts are more plausible.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 13 Jun 2019 18:00:02 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-09-04"}
