noscillating dark-matter fields can be significantly increased by making the\nthicknesses of the freely-suspended Fabry-Perot arm mirrors different in the\ntwo arms. We also discuss how small-scale Michelson interferometers, such as\nthe Fermilab holometer, could be used to perform resonant narrowband searches\nfor oscillating dark-matter fields with enhanced sensitivity to dark matter.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 14 Jun 2019 13:19:22 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 28 Jun 2019 22:34:42 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Sun, 29 Sep 2019 08:08:55 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-12-25"}
